    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA314-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu piriviṭai melinta talaimakaḷ colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said who was weakened in the time of separation.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA314">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            mutirntō riḷamai yaḻintu meytār</l>
<l>            vāḻnāḷ vakaiyaḷa vaṟiñaru millai</l>
<l>            mārip pittikat tīrita ḻalari</l>
<l>            naṟuṅkā ḻāramoṭu miṭainta mārpiṟ</l>
<l>            kuṟumpoṟik koṇṭa kommaiyam pukarppiṟ</l>
<l>            karuṅkaṇ vemmulai ñemuṅkap pullik</l>
<l>            kaḻiva tāka kaṅku leṉṟu</l>
<l>            tāmoḻi vaṉmaiyiṟ poyttaṉar vāḻiya</l>
<l>            noṭiviṭu vaṉṉa kāyviṭu kaḷḷi</l>
<l>            yalaṅkalam pāvai yēṟip pulampukoḷ</l>
<l>            puṉpuṟā vīḻpeṭaip payiru</l>
<l>            meṉṟūḻ nīḷiṭaic ceṉṟici ṉōrē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>He lied with the strength of his words, saying</l>
<l rend="indent">“Old people won’t attain youth once it is perished.</l>
<l rend="indent">No one knows the number of days to live.</l>
<l rend="indent">May the night pass in embracing,</l>
<l rend="indent2">so that [your] hot breasts with black nipples are pressed,</l>
<l rend="indent2">bright [and] round, with small spots,</l>
<l rend="indent3">to [my] chest full of sandal from the fragrant core</l>
<l rend="indent3">[and] wet-petalled blossoms of the Pittikam in the shower,”</l>
<l>– the one who has gone the long way in the sun,</l>
<l rend="indent2">where the red dove calls [its] desirable female,</l>
<l rend="indent2">conveying loneliness, rising to the swaying image(?)</l>
<l>of the Kaḷḷi tree that lets [its] unripe fruits go like a finger-snapping.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
